



Sir
Philadelphia July 5th 1775



Since my last to you by Alexander the Express nothing has Taken place in Congress that particularly Respects your Department.
By Direction of the Congress I now Transmitt you by Mr Fessenden our Return Express,1 the Rules & Articles passd by Congress for the Government of the Troops under your Command,2 I wish them safe to hand. I have not Time to add, but that I am with much Respect, Sir Your most Obedt hum. servt

John Hancock President


Should you have Occasion for a further Supply of Commissions, please to Inform me & they shall be immediately Transmitted you.

